poon mixture into prepared ramekins, arrange 4 ramekins in Varoma dish and place 2 in middle of Varoma tray. Rinse mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl. Set Varoma in position and steam <b>35 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set puddings aside and allow to cool a little (approx. 30 min). Serve warm or cold, drizzled with raspberry coulis and garnished with fresh berries."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Is it breakfast? Is it dessert? Is it an after-school snack? No matter how you choose to serve them, these puddings are made with delicious ingredients that will make you feel great about giving your loved ones - and yourself - a treat.","The puddings can be steamed in other small dishes or containers, such as dariole moulds, espresso cups, glasses, verrines or silicone muffin cups, provided they are heat-resistant. The steaming time may have to be increased by <b>5-10 minutes<b> if the containers are larger than <b>140 ml<b> each. If using ramekins or moulds no taller than <b>4 cm,<b> place them in both the Varoma dish and tray as described in the recipe. If using taller moulds, place them in Varoma dish and if they don’t all fit, steam them in <b>2 batches,<b> adding water as needed to mixing bowl.","Leftover puddings can be stored in the refrigerator for <b>2-3 days.<b> Once steamed, allow puddings to cool to room temperature, then cover and refrigerate. Serve cold, or warm before serving by steaming in the simmering basket or Varoma above <b>400 g<b> water <b><b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1.<b><b>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h","6 portions"]}